        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". And if they go into captivity before their enemies, I will command the sword thence, and it slayeth them; and I direct my eye upon them for evil, and not for good.\" The imperfects, with אם, are to be taken as futures. They do not assume what is impossible as merely hypothetical, in the sense of \"if they should hide themselves;\" but set forth what was no doubt in actual fact an impossible case, as though it were possible, in order to cut off every escape. For the cases mentioned in ",
        "children": []
